<task id="WKSP-001" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define SectionRegistration and SectionFactoryContext interfaces</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>shared-components, types</tags>
    <estimated-effort>3h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>serial</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior TypeScript/C# developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Define the SectionRegistration interface, SectionFactoryContext interface, and SectionCategory type in the shared @spaarke/ui-components library so that workspace sections can self-register with a standard contract.</goal>
    <context>
      The LegalWorkspace currently uses a monolithic buildWorkspaceConfig() factory in workspaceConfig.tsx that
      hard-wires all 5 sections (Get Started, Quick Summary, Latest Updates, To Do, Documents) with inline
      toolbar JSX and renderContent callbacks. This couples section behavior to the parent config factory.

      The new Section Registry pattern decouples sections: each section provides a SectionRegistration object
      with metadata (id, title, category, icon, default size) and a factory function that receives a
      SectionFactoryContext and returns a SectionConfig. The SectionFactoryContext provides runtime dependencies
      (webApi, userId, navigation helpers) so factories are self-contained.

      These types must live in the shared library (ADR-012) alongside the existing WorkspaceShell types so
      both LegalWorkspace and future workspaces can consume them.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - All types MUST be in @spaarke/ui-components shared library (ADR-012)
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 icon types (FluentIcon from @fluentui/react-icons) (ADR-021)
      - MUST NOT import any LegalWorkspace-specific types — these are generic contracts
      - MUST export all new types from the barrel index (src/index.ts)
      - SectionFactoryContext MUST include: webApi, userId, navigation helpers (openDialog, navigateToRecord)
      - SectionRegistration.factory MUST return SectionConfig (the existing discriminated union)
      - SectionCategory type MUST be a string union: "action-cards" | "metrics" | "content" | "embedded-app"
      - MUST NOT break any existing WorkspaceShell type exports
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspaceConfig.tsx</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the existing WorkspaceShell types.ts to understand SectionConfig, SectionType, and WorkspaceConfig interfaces that the new types must compose with.</step>
    <step id="2">Define the SectionCategory string union type: "action-cards" | "metrics" | "content" | "embedded-app". This categorizes sections for the layout wizard's section picker UI.</step>
    <step id="3">Define the SectionFactoryContext interface with runtime dependencies: webApi (IWebApi-compatible generic), userId (string), openDialog (navigateTo helper), navigateToRecord (open entity form), and any additional helpers sections need to be self-contained.</step>
    <step id="4">Define the SectionRegistration interface with: id (string), title (string), description (string), category (SectionCategory), icon (FluentIcon), defaultHeight (optional string), defaultWidth (optional "full" | "half" | "third"), and factory ((ctx: SectionFactoryContext) => SectionConfig).</step>
    <step id="5">Add the new types to the WorkspaceShell types.ts file (or a new sectionRegistry.types.ts alongside it) and ensure they are exported.</step>
    <step id="6">Update the barrel exports: ensure src/components/WorkspaceShell/index.ts re-exports the new types, and verify src/index.ts transitively exports them via the components barrel.</step>
    <step id="7">Verify the build compiles without errors by running the TypeScript compiler on the shared library.</step>
    <step id="8">Review that existing WorkspaceShell exports are unchanged — no breaking changes to current consumers.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>SectionRegistration interface is exported from @spaarke/ui-components with id, title, description, category, icon, defaultHeight, defaultWidth, and factory properties</criterion>
    <criterion>SectionFactoryContext interface is exported with webApi, userId, openDialog, and navigateToRecord members</criterion>
    <criterion>SectionCategory type is exported as "action-cards" | "metrics" | "content" | "embedded-app"</criterion>
    <criterion>factory property signature is (ctx: SectionFactoryContext) => SectionConfig</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compilation succeeds with no errors in the shared library</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
